===Noun===
'''marriage'''  (''plural:'' '''[[marriages]]''')
<!--Note:  If you wish to edit this definition PLEASE keep in mind issues of POV and NPOV; please read up on some of the conversation from the talk page and discuss it on IRC first. -->

# An [[institution]] through which people join together their lives in [[emotional]] and [[economic]] ways through forming a [[household]]. It often confers rights and obligations with respect to raising children, holding property, sexual behavior, [[kinship]] ties, tribal membership, relationship to society, [[inheritance]], emotional intimacy, and [[love]]. This institution may be recognized by society, a church, and/or a government.  In Western cultures marriage is traditionally a [[monogamy|monogamous]] union between one man and one woman as [[husband]] and [[wife]] respectively. In most other societies [[polygamy|polygamous]] unions are traditional, where either a man may have multiple  wives ([[polygyny]]) or, more rarely, a woman multiple husbands ([[polyandry]]). In some societies and subcultures, same-sex unions between two women or two men ([[w:same-sex marriage|same-sex marriage]]), or unions among multiple men and women ([[w:group marriage|group marriage]]) are recognized, though recognition of such unions is not universal, and even the validity of labelling these unions 'marriage' is contested.
#: '''Examples'''
#* ''Conservative Western Christians believe that '''marriage''' should be limited to the union of one man and one woman.''
#* ''The king of Swaziland recently entered into '''marriage''' with his thirteenth wife.''
#* ''The Netherlands allows '''marriage''' between same-sex couples.''
# A wedding.
#* ''You are cordially invited to the '''marriage''' of John Smith and Jane Doe.''
# A close union.
# A joining of two parts.

